g.text: $ g4x-helpers update_bin --help
Usage: g4x-helpers update_bin [OPTIONS]
Update existing G4X-viewer .bin file with new metadata
│ * --g4x-data -i DIRECTORY Directory containing G4X-data for a single │
│ sample [required] │
│ --sample-id -s TEXT Sample ID (used for naming outputs) │
│ --output -o DIRECTORY Output directory used. Will edit G4X-data │
│ in-place if not provided. │
│ * --metadata FILE Path to metadata table where clustering │
│ and/or embedding information will be │
│ extracted. Table must contain a header. │
│ [required] │
│ --cellid-key TEXT Column name in metadata containing cell │
│ IDs that match with bin_file. If not │
│ provided, assumes that first column in │
│ metadata contains the cell IDs. │
│ --cluster-key TEXT Column name in metadata containing cluster │
│ IDs. Automatically assigns new colors if │
│ cluster_color_key is not provided. If not │
│ provided, skips updating cluster IDs. │
│ --cluster-color-key TEXT Column name in metadata containing cluster │
│ colors. Colors must be provided as hex │
│ codes. If provided, cluster_key must also │
│ be provided. If not provided, skips │
│ updating cluster colors. │
│ --emb-key TEXT Column name in metadata containing │
│ embedding. Parser will look for │
│ {emb_key}_1 and {emb_key}_2. If not │
│ provided, skips updating embedding. │
│ --help -h Show this message and exit. │
